<edge source="Global Tech Index" target="Market Selloff">
  <data key="d7">17.0</data>
  <data key="d8">**Global Tech Index and Market Selloff**

The **Global Tech Index**, a benchmark for the technology sector, has been declining as part of the broader **Market Selloff**. This decline is driven by investor concerns over rising interest rates, which have led to a decrease in demand for stocks and other assets. The market selloff is characterized by widespread selling pressure across various sectors, including technology.

Investors are seeking safe-haven assets, such as gold, during this tumultuous period, causing the price of gold to rise. However, the impact on the Global Tech Index has been more pronounced due to its sensitivity to interest rates and investor sentiment. Despite efforts to mitigate the effects, the decline in the index continues, contributing to the overall market selloff.

It is essential to note that the specific details surrounding the Market Selloff may vary depending on individual perspectives or historical events. However, it is clear that the **Global Tech Index** is an integral part of this broader phenomenon, with its performance closely tied to investor concerns and interest rate fluctuations.&lt;SEP&gt;The decline in the Global Tech Index is part of the broader market selloff driven by investor concerns.`&lt;SEP&gt;The decline in the Global Tech Index is part of the broader market selloff driven by investor concerns.&lt;SEP&gt;The decline in the Global Tech Index is driven by investor concerns over rising interest rates and regulatory uncertainty.&lt;SEP&gt;The decline in the Global Tech Index is part of the broader market selloff driven by investor concerns.&lt;SEP&gt;The decline in the Global Tech Index is part of the broader market selloff driven by investor concerns.&lt;SEP&gt;The decline in the Global Tech Index contributed to the broader market selloff driven by investor concerns over interest rates and regulatory uncertainty.</data>
