<edge source="Market Selloff" target="Gold Futures">
  <data key="d7">11.0</data>
  <data key="d8">**Market Selloff and Gold Futures: A Safe-Haven Asset**

The Market Selloff, a period of significant economic downturn, triggered a surge in demand for gold futures as investors sought safe-haven assets. This phenomenon is rooted in the inherent value of gold as a store of wealth and its ability to provide a hedge against market volatility.

During this tumultuous period, gold prices rose substantially as investors flocked to gold futures in search of protection from potential losses. The stability and durability of gold make it an attractive asset during times of economic uncertainty. As investors sought safe-haven assets, the price of gold futures increased, reflecting the growing demand for a secure store of value.

Investors' decision to seek safe-haven assets was not solely driven by the Market Selloff, but rather was a response to the underlying market conditions that were conducive to asset diversification and risk mitigation. The fact that investors sought protection from potential losses underscores the importance of gold as a hedge against market volatility.

It is worth noting that the rise in gold prices during this period can be attributed to multiple factors, including but not limited to, investor sentiment, market conditions, and global economic trends. However, it is clear that the demand for safe-haven assets such as gold futures was a key driver of the price increase.&lt;SEP&gt;Gold prices rose as investors sought safe-haven assets during the market selloff.</data>
  <data key="d9">crisis investment,market reaction,safe-haven asset,safe-haven investment</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-8a83bcdf6e7b7269cfd17b4f21457de8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1e7cec156f57837e8d25cbe83a6db45f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-41be59e9bae9e87a716afd8b5a9e9ee1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-39206ec5906f23d68e051b1df74d3ca7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-942b136689124792272bc32a2898842c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5618eb566fb322ada0eb69bef88a7581&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1e6839b81653aa7c9b7ec794f3447380&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3c4967b23b72f04d5c4ef37149d21ede&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c0cd3e323fc2a43e461d7af757b08706</data>
