<edge source="Noah Carter" target="100m Sprint Record">
  <data key="d7">20.0</data>
  <data key="d8">**The 100m Sprint Record Held by Noah Carter**

Noah Carter made history at the World Athletics Championship in Tokyo, breaking the 100m sprint record. This achievement marked a significant milestone in his illustrious career. The event was held under the oversight of the World Athletics Federation, which governs and oversees high-profile competitions like this one.

It is worth noting that Carter's record-breaking performance was met with notable circumstances surrounding the use of cutting-edge carbon-fiber spikes. While initial reports indicated that these advanced running shoes played no role in Carter's triumph, subsequent details revealed their involvement in securing a new world record. Photographic evidence from the championship suggests they were indeed worn during the event.

The role of these specialized spikes in Carter's achievement is still unclear. It remains uncertain whether they contributed to an enhanced performance or if they merely provided support for his already exceptional abilities. However, one thing is certain – Noah Carter's dedication and skill within the world of athletics have earned him a place in history with this remarkable record.

The championship itself was a high-profile competition that drew top athletes from around the globe. Held in Tokyo, it served as the backdrop for this remarkable achievement, making Carter's record a testament to his skill and dedication.&lt;SEP&gt;Noah Carter set a new 100m sprint record at the championship.</data>
